354
00:28:06,240 --> 00:28:08,240
I don't care what's wrong with her.

355
00:28:09,480 --> 00:28:11,480
Nueng, you need to understand,

356
00:28:11,720 --> 00:28:13,480
That grandma is getting old these days.

357
00:28:15,240 --> 00:28:17,000
Hey Sam, listen to me.

358
00:28:18,240 --> 00:28:21,480
Grandma will not easily get sick and die. Believe me.

359
00:28:22,000 --> 00:28:23,240
If grandma isn't around anymore,

360
00:28:23,480 --> 00:28:26,720
Will you regret you weren't nicer to her?

361
00:28:30,720 --> 00:28:32,480
Aww. I have to go.

362
00:28:41,000 --> 00:28:42,000
Nueng.

363
00:28:47,000 --> 00:28:48,720
I'll drive you home.

364
00:28:49,000 --> 00:28:51,240
No need. I can get home myself.

365
00:28:52,240 --> 00:28:54,480
Grandma loves you very much.

366
00:28:56,480 --> 00:28:58,000
And I want you to ...

367
00:28:58,000 --> 00:28:58,954
To reconcile with grandma?

368
00:29:00,480 --> 00:29:01,480
Yes.

369
00:29:02,240 --> 00:29:05,000
